If the book won an award, I consider the award carefully. Many (eg. Hugo or Nebula) have become negative indicators of readability (books that appeal to a fairly insular group of award givers, rather than the general reader base).
An interesting synopsis can get me interested in a book.  Also word of mouth from friends can get me to try a book.
